nmap --script dos -p 2222 <target.com or ip> <enter>

nmap --script dos -p 2222 10.11.17.140
Seul mon port 2222 est ouvert


1.Config portsentry
First, we have to edit the /etc/default/portsentry file

TCP_MODE="atcp"
UDP_MODE="audp"
After, edit the file /etc/portsentry/portsentry.conf

BLOCK_UDP="1"
BLOCK_TCP="1"
Comment the current KILL_ROUTE and uncomment the following one:

KILL_ROUTE="/sbin/iptables -I INPUT -s $TARGET$ -j DROP"
Comment the following line:

KILL_HOSTS_DENY="ALL: $TARGET$ : DENY

2.We can now restart the service to make changes effectives
sudo service portsentry restart

3.Test ports scans 
nmap --script dos -Pn 10.11.17.140
